      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 255: Changing `Task { @MainActor in ... }` to an unisolated `Task` and then manually dispatching back to the main queue weakens actor/thread-safety for this view model. The continuation after `await` now runs off-main until the dispatch, and future edits in this block can easily mutate `tempAccount`, `pendingAuthResults`, or `uiState` from the wrong executor. Since this is UI state, keep the task isolated to `MainActor`; the awaited account creation will still suspend without blocking the main thread.\n```suggestion\nTask { @MainActor in\n    do {\n        tempAccount \u003d try await accountsService.createTemporaryAccount()\n        let bufferedResults \u003d pendingAuthResults\n        pendingAuthResults.removeAll()\n        for result in bufferedResults where result.accountId \u003d\u003d tempAccount {\n            updateDeviceAuthState(result: result)\n        }\n    } catch {\n        withAnimation { uiState \u003d .error(message: LinkDeviceError.networkError) }\n    }\n}\n```",
