      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 175: Deferring `callDetails(withCallId:accountId:)` to an async barrier can race with subsequent daemon state changes before the incoming call is registered. If the daemon updates or removes the call before this closure runs, the initial incoming notification may be dropped by the `guard`, which is especially risky for the latency-sensitive path being changed. Capture the daemon-provided details synchronously, then move only the state mutation/notification work onto the serialized queue.\n```suggestion\nguard let callDictionary \u003d self.callsAdapter.callDetails(withCallId: callId, accountId: accountId) else { return }\nqueueHelper.barrierAsync { [weak self] in\n    guard let self \u003d self else { return }\n    _ \u003d self.callManagementService.addOrUpdateCall(callId: callId,\n                                                   callState: .incoming,\n                                                   callDictionary: callDictionary,\n                                                   mediaList: withMedia,\n                                                   notifyIncoming: true)\n}\n```",
